title.narrative: To improve access and quality of health care in Benin, through a more integrated, effective, and resilient health system

description.narrative: Benin - RSSH - Conseil National de Lutte contre le VIH/SIDA, la Tuberculose, le Paludisme, les Hépatites, les Infections sexuellement transmissibles et les Epidémies - CNLS-TP. This program has the following goals: Help improve public health by ensuring Benin has an effective, resilient health system.. The objectives of this program are: Improve human resources management at the operational and community levels.. Strengthen the National Health Management Information System (NHMIS) and the activity monitoring and evaluation (M&E) system to support informed decision-making.. Introduce an effective procurement and supply management (PSM) system for health supplies.. Expand national coverage of high-quality services and service delivery.. Strengthen institutional capacities and intervention coordination.
